#   path or is re-evaluated — owed to P9 (broader concurrent/repeated test).
#
# ADDITIVE (§11.4.122) — by CONCATENATION, not a native include:
#   Dante v1.4.4 has NO `include` directive (CONFIRMED: `sockd -V` rejects both
#   `include: "..."` and `include "..."` with a syntax error —
#   qa-results/p4_templates/dante_parse.txt). So the compiler builds the deployed
#   sockd.conf by APPENDING these rendered `route` blocks AFTER the SHIPPED
#   config/dante/sockd.conf content verbatim (which keeps internal: :51080,
#   external: proxy-dante, socksmethod: none, and its client/socks pass rules
#   exactly as today). The base lines are preserved unchanged; this file ONLY
#   ADDS per-tunnel egress `route` blocks — it never rewrites or removes them.
#   The `route { ... }` block syntax below VERIFIES clean (`sockd -V` exit 0).
#
# STATUS: DESIGN / template only — NOT yet wired into a running stack.
